Introduction

tcplfit2 package provides functions for basic concentration-response curve fitting used in the ‘tcpl’ package. It is a substitute for the original tcplFit() function (and sub-functions) in previous versions of tcpl and allows a wider variety of concentration-response models. This package includes models from the ‘BMDExpress’ software and the output includes a calculation of the bmd (Benchmark Dose or Concentration) value.

Requirements:

R (>= 3.5.0)
R packages required: stats, methods, numDeriv, RColorBrewer, stringr
R packages suggested: knitr, rmarkdown, stringi

Installation

You may install this package from GitHub or CRAN. GitHub has access to a more recent development version of this package that might includes features that are not officially included in the version on CRAN.

1. Install from GitHub (need “devtools” package)
devtools::install_git("https://github.com/USEPA/CompTox-ToxCast-tcplFit2.git")

2. Install from CRAN, version 0.1.5 released 2023-04-06
install.packages("tcplfit2")

